div.div:
The diagram provides a mechanism to store and encrypt data in an Amazon Simple Storage.
1. A Key Management Service (KMS) customer managed key is created to encrypt the data.
2. KMS is a managed service for creating and controlling the encryption keys that are used to encrypt data. The key that you are used to encryption keys that are used to encrypt data. The keys that you
create in AWS KMS are protected by FIPS validated hardware security model(HSM)
3. Data is stored in an S3 bucket, Amazon S3 bucket is an object storage service that stores data sa objects withing buckets. An object is a file and any metadata that describes the file.
A bucket is an container for objects.
4. The S3 bucket default encryption is configured to use the KMS key to encrypt the data.
5. A bucket policy is used to force the encryption of uploaded objects. A bucket policy is a resource-based policy used to grant access permissions to an s3 bucket and the object in it.
6. The AWS Command Line Interface is used to manage encryption configuration for the S3 bucket.
